frameDefinitions: A Speaker conventionally uses a particular Term to refer to an Entity.
An Entity stands out perceptually in comparison to other members of its type.
In the course of history, an Event or Entity is taken to have importance or significance.
An Entity is evaluated for whether or not it belongs to a particular Reference_category in a context where its category membership is doubtful.
An Entity is obscure, unnotable, and in general little-known.
The Behavior of an Evaluee is described in terms of the reaction it deserves from somebody, such as praise, blame or admiration.
frameExamples: The pattern of conservation is similar to that found in C1_1, therefore we have <t>termed</t> this domain DC1 for divergent C1 domain.
Pilot Mountain in NC is very <t>prominent</t>.
Throughout the campaign activists have <t>made</t> financial <t>history</t> as one by one major corporations have yielded to protester power

It can be hard to get your money back after discovering you've bought a <t>bogus</t>
autograph for hundreds or thousands of dollars!
Geoffrey Rush was <t>little</t> <t>known</t> outside his native Australia when he soared to international prominence.
It was <t>honorable</t> of you to help that person.
listRoleDefinitions: The type of <fen>Entity</fen> that is conventionally referred to by a <fen>Term</fen>.
The linguistic sign that is used for referring to a type of <fen>Entity</fen>.
The speaker or speech community that uses a <fen>Term</fen> to refer to a particular <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which the saliency <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
The feature of the <fen>Entity</fen> which is under discussion, namely perceptual salience.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular salience.
This role refers to the location where the <fen>Entity</fen> has a prominence of some <fen>Attribute</fen>.
This role identifies the event which occurs to create history.
This role identifies the entity, concrete or abstract.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
This role identifies where the event takes place.
The <fen>Entity</fen> that is being evaluated in terms of whether it is an instance of the <fen>Reference_category</fen>.
The type relative to which the <fen>Entity</fen> is evaluated.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which is not widely known and rather obscure.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is not well known.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is not famous.
The <fen>Behavior</fen> of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged as worthy of a particular reaction.
This role indicates the <fen>Behavior</fen> on which the assessment of praiseworthiness is based.
listRoleExamples: Because of that shift, physicists call <fex>this effect</fex> the 'gravitational red shift.'
The French term this plant <fex>Petit Chêne</fex>, from the shape of the leaves.
<fex>Mathematicians</fex> call this subject 'arithmetic,' reserving the word 'algebra' for the more advanced aspects of the subject.
If you are asked to search for the plus sign with red-vertical and green-horizontal elements, <fex>all the red and green plus signs</fex> may seem to become salient.
The diagram, (a frequency distribution chart) shows a <fex>prominently</fex> conspicuous region of stars that extend from the extremely bright and hot stars to the faint and cool variety.
The affection for American culture seemed more prominent <fex>last year</fex>.
<fex>The bomb found at the US Embassy in Berlin</fex> was fake.
Certain academic works are obscure <fex>only in North America</fex>.
It was commendable <fex>of Lisa</fex> to give so much to charity.
